(firstQuint)Morbimortality in Older Patients Undergoing Urgent Abdominal Surgery.

 the investigor will register the morbimotality after 6 months of follow up, in patient older than 65 year old using the CRISTAL score modify, undergoing abdominal surgery.

 The measure the investigators are using are: Barthel scale, Frail score, Mininutritional score, Clavien-Dindo modify, frailty.

 The objective of the study is to predict morbimortality with Cristal score modify.

